1public class GLBL_RollupSummaryUtility {
2     
3    //the following class will be used to house the field names
4    //and desired operations
5    public class fieldDefinition {
6        public String operation {get;set;}
7        public String childField {get;set;}
8        public String parentField {get;set;}
9         
10        public fieldDefinition (String o, String c, String p) {
11            operation = o;
12            childField = c;
13            parentField = p;
14        }
15    }
16     
17    public static void rollUpTrigger(list<fieldDefinition> fieldDefinitions,
18    list<sObject> records, String childObject, String childParentLookupField, 
19    String parentObject, String queryFilter) {
20         
21        //Limit the size of list by using Sets which do not contain duplicate
22        //elements prevents hitting governor limits
23        set<Id> parentIds = new set<Id>();
24         
25        for(sObject s : records) {
26            parentIds.add((Id)s.get(childParentLookupField));
27        }
28         
29        //populate query text strings to be used in child aggregrator and 
30        //parent value assignment
31        String fieldsToAggregate = '';
32        String parentFields = '';
33         
34        for(fieldDefinition d : fieldDefinitions) {
35            fieldsToAggregate += d.operation + '(' + d.childField + ') ' + 
36            ', ';
37            parentFields += d.parentField + ', ';
38        }
39         
40        //Using dynamic SOQL with aggergate results to populate parentValueMap
41        String aggregateQuery = 'Select ' + fieldsToAggregate + 
42        childParentLookupField + ' from ' + childObject + ' where  ' + 
43        childParentLookupField + ' IN :parentIds ' + queryFilter + ' ' +
44        ' group by ' + childParentLookupField;
45         
46        //Map will contain one parent record Id per one aggregate object
47        map<Id, AggregateResult> parentValueMap = 
48        new map <Id, AggregateResult>();
49         
50        for(AggregateResult q : Database.query(aggregateQuery)){
51            parentValueMap.put((Id)q.get(childParentLookupField), q);
52        }
53         
54        //list of parent object records to update
55        list<sObject> parentsToUpdate = new list<sObject>();
56         
57        String parentQuery = 'select ' + parentFields + ' Id ' +
58         ' from ' + parentObject + ' where Id IN :parentIds';
59         
60        //for each affected parent object, retrieve aggregate results and 
61        //for each field definition add aggregate value to parent field
62        for(sObject s : Database.query(parentQuery)) {
63             
64            Integer row = 0; //row counter reset for every parent record
65            for(fieldDefinition d : fieldDefinitions) {
66                String field = 'expr' + row.format();
67                AggregateResult r = parentValueMap.get(s.Id);
68                //r will be null if no records exist 
69                //(e.g. last record deleted)
70                if(r != null) { 
71                    Decimal value = ((Decimal)r.get(field) == null ) ? 0 : 
72                        (Decimal)r.get(field);
73                    s.put(d.parentField, value);
74                } else {
75                    s.put(d.parentField, 0);
76                }
77                row += 1; //plus 1 for every field definition after first
78            }
79            parentsToUpdate.add(s);
80        }
81         
82        //if parent records exist, perform update of all parent records 
83        //with a single DML statement
84        if(parentsToUpdate.Size() > 0) {
85            update parentsToUpdate;
86        }
87         
88    }
89 
90}

27/**
28 * Serializes and Deserializes SObject records and related child and referenced records using the Apex JSON support
29 *
30 *   See https://github.com/afawcett/apex-sobjectdataloader for known issues, restrictions and TODO's
31 *
32 **/
33public with sharing class GLBL_SobjectDataLoader 
34{
35    /**
36     * Configuration uses a Fluent method design (http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fluent_interface), 
37     **/
38    public class SerializeConfig
39    {
40        protected Set<Schema.SObjectField> followRelationships;
41        protected Set<Schema.SObjectField> followChildRelationships;
42        protected Set<Schema.SObjectField> omitFields;
43        
44        public SerializeConfig()
45        {    
46            followRelationships = new Set<Schema.SObjectField>();
47            followChildRelationships = new Set<Schema.SObjectField>();
48            omitFields = new Set<Schema.SObjectField>();             
49        }
50        
51        /**
52         * Provide a field that represents the lookup relationship the serializer should follow
53         **/
54        public SerializeConfig follow(Schema.SObjectField relationshipField)
55        {
56            followRelationships.add(relationshipField);
57            return this;
58        }
59        
60        /**
61         * Provide a field that represents a parent child relationship the serializer should follow
62         **/
63        public SerializeConfig followChild(Schema.SObjectField relationshipField)
64        {
65            followChildRelationships.add(relationshipField);
66            return this;
67        }
68        
69        /**
70         * Provide a field that the serializer should omit from the serialized output
71         **/
72        public SerializeConfig omit(Schema.SObjectField omitField)
73        {
74            omitFields.add(omitField);
75            if(followRelationships.contains(omitField))
76                followRelationships.remove(omitField);
77            if(followChildRelationships.contains(omitField))
78                followChildRelationships.remove(omitField);
79            return this;
80        }
81        
82        /** 
83         * Automatically configure (removes all previous configuration)
84         *  Skip known system lookup and child relationships but include the rest (direct children only) upto certain depth, 
85         *  Caller can always add or omit specific via follow or omit methods
86         **/
87        public SerializeConfig auto(Schema.SObjectType sObjectType)
88        {
89            followRelationships = new Set<Schema.SObjectField>();
90            followChildRelationships = new Set<Schema.SObjectField>();
91            omitFields = new Set<Schema.SObjectField>();
92            Set<Schema.SObjectType> searched = new Set<Schema.SObjectType>();
93            searchRelationships(sObjectType, 0, 0, true, searched);    
94            return this;    
95        }
96        
97        /**
98         * Seek out recursively relationships
99         **/
100        private void searchRelationships(Schema.SObjectType sObjectType, Integer lookupDepth, Integer childDepth, Boolean searchChildren, Set<Schema.SObjectType> searched)
101        {        
102            // Stop infinite recursion    
103            if(searched.contains(sObjectType) || lookupDepth > 2 || childDepth > 3) // TODO: Make max depth configurable
104                return;
105            searched.add(sObjectType);
106            Schema.DescribeSObjectResult sObjectDescribe = sObjectType.getDescribe();
107                        
108            // Following children? (only set for descendents of the top level object)
109            if(searchChildren)
110            {
111                List<Schema.ChildRelationship> childRelationships = sObjectDescribe.getChildRelationships();
112                for(Schema.ChildRelationship childRelationship : childRelationships)
113                {
114                    // Determine which child relationships to automatically follow
115                    String childRelationshipName = childRelationship.getRelationshipName();
116                    if(childRelationshipName==null || 
117                       childRelationshipWhitelist.contains(childRelationshipName)) // Skip relationships without names and those whitelisted
118                        continue;
119                    if(childRelationshipName.endsWith('Histories')) // Skip relationships ending in Histories (TODO: consider a RegEx approach?)
120                        continue;
121                    if(!childRelationship.isCascadeDelete()) // Skip relationships for none owned records (aka only follow master-detail relationships)
122                        continue;
123                    followChild(childRelationship.getField()).
124                        searchRelationships(childRelationship.getChildSObject(), lookupDepth, childDepth+1, true, searched);
125                }
126            }
127                            
128            // Follow lookup relationships to long as they have not previously been added as child references and are not whitelisted
129            Map<String, Schema.SObjectField> sObjectFields = sObjectDescribe.fields.getMap();
130            for(Schema.SObjectField sObjectField : sObjectFields.values())
131                if(sObjectField.getDescribe().getType() == Schema.DisplayType.Reference) 
132                    if(!followChildRelationships.contains(sObjectField) && !relationshipWhitelist.contains(sObjectField.getDescribe().getName()))
133                        follow(sObjectField).
134                            searchRelationships(sObjectField.getDescribe().getReferenceTo()[0], lookupDepth+1, childDepth, false, searched);
135        }
136
137        // Standard fields that are not included when using the auto config
138        private Set<String> relationshipWhitelist = 
139            new Set<String>
140                { 'OwnerId',
141                  'CreatedById',
142                  'LastModifiedById',
143                  'RecordTypeId',
144                  'PersonContactId'
145                };
146                
147        // Standard child relationships that are not included when using the auto config
148        private Set<String> childRelationshipWhitelist = 
149            new Set<String> 
150                { 'Shares', 
151                  'ProcessInstances', 
152                  'ProcessSteps', 
153                  'Tasks', 
154                  'ActivityHistories', 
155                  'Attachments', 
156                  'FeedSubscriptionsForEntity', 
157                  'Events', 
158                  'Notes', 
159                  'NotesAndAttachments', 
160                  'OpenActivities', 
161                  'Histories', 
162                  'Feeds',
163                  'PersonEmailStatuses',
164                  'OpenActivities',
165                  'PersonOpenActivities'};    
166    }
167

169    /**
170     * Serialize the given records using the default configuration (see SerializeConfig.auto)
171     **/
172    public static String serialize(Set<Id> ids)
173    {
174        // Serialize based on no prior knowledge of the objects
175        if(ids==null || ids.size()==0)
176            throw new SerializerException('List of Ids cannot be null or empty.');
177        return serialize(ids, new SerializeConfig().auto(new List<Id>(ids)[0].getSObjectType()));
178    }
179    
180    /**
181     * Serialize the given records using the given configuration
182     **/
183    public static String serialize(Set<Id> ids, SerializeConfig strategy)
184    {            
185        // Validate parameters
186        if(ids==null || ids.size()==0)
187            throw new SerializerException('List of Ids cannot be null or empty.');
188            
189        // Container to bundle record sets into 
190        RecordsBundle recordsToBundle = new RecordsBundle();
191        recordsToBundle.recordSetBundles = new List<RecordSetBundle>();        
192        recordsToBundle.recordSetBundlesByType = new Map<String, RecordSetBundle>();
193        
194        // Begin recursive serialize from given records through to related records
195        Schema.SObjectType sObjectType = new List<Id>(ids)[0].getSObjectType();
196        serialize(ids, sObjectType, null, strategy, 0, 0, recordsToBundle);
197                
198        // Serialise the records bundle container        
199        return JSON.serialize(recordsToBundle);                 
200    }
201
202    /**
203     * Deserialize the given JSON record set bundle
204     **/
205    public static Set<Id> deserialize(String recordsBundleAsJSON)
206    {
207        return deserialize(recordsBundleAsJSON, null);
208    }
209        
210    /**
211     * Deserialize the given JSON record set bundle utilising the given callback
212     **/
213    public static Set<Id> deserialize(String recordsBundleAsJSON, IDeserializeCallback callback)
214    {
215        // Desearialise the records bundle
216        RecordsBundle recordsBundle = (RecordsBundle) 
217            JSON.deserialize(recordsBundleAsJSON, GLBL_SobjectDataLoader.RecordsBundle.class);
218        
219        // Map to track original ID's against the new SObject record instances being inserted
220        Map<Id, SObject> recordsByOriginalId = new Map<Id, SObject>();
221        
222        // Record set bundles are already ordered in dependency order due to serialisation approach
223        Map<String, Schema.SObjectType> sObjectsByType = Schema.getGlobalDescribe();
224        for(RecordSetBundle recordSetBundle : recordsBundle.recordSetBundles)
225        {
226            // Determine lookup / relationship fields to update prior to inserting these records
227            Schema.SObjectType sObjectType = sObjectsByType.get(recordSetBundle.ObjectType);
228            Map<String, Schema.SObjectField> sObjectFields = sObjectType.getDescribe().fields.getMap();
229            List<Schema.SObjectField> relationshipsFields = new List<Schema.SObjectField>();
230            for(Schema.SObjectField sObjectField : sObjectFields.values())
231                if(sObjectField.getDescribe().getType() == Schema.DisplayType.Reference) 
232                    relationshipsFields.add(sObjectField);
233                                    
234            // Prepare records for insert
235            List<SObject> recordsToInsert = new List<SObject>();
236            List<UnresolvedReferences> unresolvedReferencesByRecord = new List<UnresolvedReferences>(); 
237            for(SObject orignalRecord : recordSetBundle.Records)
238            {
239                // Clone the deserialised SObject to remove the original Id prior to inserting it
240                SObject newRecord = orignalRecord.clone();
241                recordsToInsert.add(newRecord);
242                // Map the new cloned record to its old Id (once inserted this can be used to obtain the new id)
243                recordsByOriginalId.put(orignalRecord.Id, newRecord);
244                // Update foreign key references / lookups / master-detail relationships
245                if(relationshipsFields.size()>0)
246                {
247                    Set<Schema.SObjectField> unresolvedFieldReferences = new Set<Schema.SObjectField>(); 
248                    for(Schema.SObjectField sObjectField : relationshipsFields)
249                    {                            
250                        // Obtained original related record Id and search map over new records by old Ids
251                        Id oldRelatedRecordId = (Id) orignalRecord.get(sObjectField);
252                        SObject newRelatedRecord = recordsByOriginalId.get(oldRelatedRecordId);
253                        if(newRelatedRecord!=null)
254                            newRecord.put(sObjectField, newRelatedRecord.Id);
255                        else
256                            unresolvedFieldReferences.add(sObjectField);
257                    }
258                    // Retain a list of records with unresolved references
259                    if(unresolvedFieldReferences.size()>0)
260                    {
261                        UnresolvedReferences unresolvedReferences = new UnresolvedReferences();
262                        unresolvedReferences.Record = newRecord;
263                        unresolvedReferences.References = unresolvedFieldReferences;
264                        unresolvedReferencesByRecord.add(unresolvedReferences);
265                    }    
266                }
267            }            
268            
269            // Let the caller attempt to resolve any references the above could not
270            if(callback!=null && unresolvedReferencesByRecord.size()>0)
271                callback.unresolvedReferences(sObjectType, unresolvedReferencesByRecord);
272            
273            if(callback!=null)
274                callback.cloneMapHandler(recordsByOriginalId);
275
276            // Insert cloned deserialised records
277            recordSetBundle.Records = recordsToInsert;
278            insert recordSetBundle.Records;
279        }
280        
281        // Return Id list from the first bundle set
282        return new Map<Id, SObject>(recordsBundle.recordSetBundles[0].Records).keySet();
283    }
284            
285    private static void serialize(Set<ID> ids, Schema.SObjectType sObjectType, Schema.SObjectField queryByIdField, SerializeConfig config, Integer lookupDepth, Integer childDepth, RecordsBundle recordsToBundle)
286    {        
287        // Config?
288        if(config==null)
289            throw new SerializerException('Must pass a valid SerializeConfig instance.');
290        // Stop infinite recursion
291        if(lookupDepth > 3 || childDepth > 3) // TODO: Make max depth configurable
292            return;
293            
294        // Describe object and determine fields to serialize
295        Schema.DescribeSObjectResult sObjectDesc = sObjectType.getDescribe();
296        Map<String, Schema.SObjectField> sObjectFields = sObjectDesc.fields.getMap();
297        List<Schema.SObjectField> sObjectFieldsToSerialize = listFieldsToSerialize(sObjectFields, config);
298                        
299        // Query records to serialize
300        String fieldList = null;
301        for(Schema.SObjectField sObjectField : sObjectFieldsToSerialize)
302            fieldList = fieldList == null ? sObjectField.getDescribe().getName() : fieldList + ',' + sObjectField.getDescribe().getName();
303        String query = String.format('select {0} from {1} where {2} in :ids order by {2}', 
304            new List<String> { fieldList, sObjectDesc.getName(), queryByIdField == null ? 'id' : queryByIdField.getDescribe().getName(), 'Name' });
305        Map<Id, SObject> recordsToSerializeById = new Map<Id, SObject>(Database.query(query));
306        if(recordsToSerializeById.size()==0)
307            return;
308        
309        // Any lookup relationships to folow?
310        Set<Schema.SObjectField> sObjectFollowRelationships = config.followRelationships.clone();
311        sObjectFollowRelationships.retainAll(sObjectFields.values());
312        if(sObjectFollowRelationships.size()>0)
313        {                
314            // Build list of ID's for each related record
315            Map<Schema.DescribeFieldResult, Set<Id>> relationshipsByField = new Map<Schema.DescribeFieldResult, Set<Id>>(); 
316            for(Schema.SObjectField sObjectField : sObjectFollowRelationships)
317                relationShipsByField.put(sObjectField.getDescribe(), new Set<Id>() );            
318            for(SObject recordToSerialize : recordsToSerializeById.values())
319            {
320                for(Schema.DescribeFieldResult relationshipField : relationshipsByField.keySet())
321                {
322                    Id relatedId = (Id) recordToSerialize.get(relationshipField.getSObjectField());
323                    if(relatedId!=null)
324                        relationshipsByField.get(relationshipField).add(relatedId);
325                }
326            }
327            // Serialise related records
328            for(Schema.DescribeFieldResult relationshipField : relationshipsByField.keySet())
329            {
330                Set<Id> relatedRecordIds = relationshipsByField.get(relationshipField);
331                if(relatedRecordIds.size()>0)
332                    serialize(relatedRecordIds, relationshipField.getReferenceTo()[0], null, config, lookupDepth+1, childDepth, recordsToBundle);                    
333            }
334        }
335                    
336        // Add records to applicable record set bundle
337        RecordSetBundle recordSetBundle = recordsToBundle.recordSetBundlesByType.get(sObjectDesc.getName());
338        if(recordSetBundle!=null)
339        {
340            recordSetBundle.Records.addAll(recordsToSerializeById.values());
341        }
342        else if(recordSetBundle==null)
343        {
344            recordSetBundle = new RecordSetBundle();
345            recordSetBundle.ObjectType = sObjectDesc.getName();
346            recordSetBundle.Records = recordsToSerializeById.values();
347            recordsToBundle.recordSetBundles.add(recordSetBundle);
348            recordsToBundle.recordSetBundlesByType.put(recordSetBundle.ObjectType, recordSetBundle);
349        }
350                
351        // Any child relationships to follow?
352        List<Schema.ChildRelationship> childRelationships = sObjectDesc.getChildRelationships();
353        for(Schema.ChildRelationship childRelationship : childRelationships)
354        { 
355            // Is this a child relationship we have been asked to follow?
356            Schema.SObjectType childSObjectType = childRelationship.getChildSObject();
357            if(config.followChildRelationships.contains(childRelationship.getField()))
358                serialize(recordsToSerializeById.keySet(), childSObjectType, childRelationship.getField(), config, lookupDepth, childDepth+1, recordsToBundle);
359        }
360    }
361    
362    private static List<Schema.SObjectField> listFieldsToSerialize(Map<String, Schema.SObjectField> sObjectFields, SerializeConfig config)
363    {
364        // Filter fields to serialise
365        List<Schema.SObjectField> serializeFields = new List<Schema.SObjectField>(); 
366        List<String> fieldNames = new List<String>(sObjectFields.keySet());
367        fieldNames.sort();
368        for(String fieldName : fieldNames)
369        {
370            // Skip fields indicated in config
371            Schema.SObjectField sObjectField = sObjectFields.get(fieldName);
372            if(config.omitFields!=null && config.omitFields.contains(sObjectField))
373                continue;
374            // Skip read only fields, such as auto numbers and formula fields
375            Schema.DescribeFieldResult sObjectFieldDescribe = sObjectField.getDescribe();
376            if(sObjectFieldDescribe.isAutoNumber() ||
377               sObjectFieldDescribe.isCalculated())
378               continue;    
379            // Skip lookup fields not in either of the follow lists
380            if(sObjectFieldDescribe.getType() == Schema.DisplayType.Reference)
381                if(!(config.followRelationships.contains(sObjectField) ||
382                     config.followChildRelationships.contains(sObjectField)))
383                   continue;
384            // Serialize this field..                        
385            serializeFields.add(sObjectField);
386        }            
387        return serializeFields;    
388    }
389

5public class GLBL_TriggerHandler 
6{
7    /**
8     *   Enum representing each of before/after CRUD events on Sobjects
9     */
10    public enum Evt 
11    {
12        afterdelete, afterinsert, afterundelete,
13        afterupdate, beforedelete, beforeinsert, beforeupdate   
14    }
15
16    /*
17     *   Simplistic handler to implement on any of the event. It doesn't require or enforces any pattern except the
18     *   method name to be "handle()".
19     */
20    public interface HandlerInterface
21    {
22        void handle();          
23    } 
24
25    // Internal mapping of handlers
26    map<String, list<HandlerInterface>> eventHandlerMapping = new map<String, list<HandlerInterface>>();
27
28    /**
29     *   Core API to bind handlers with events
30     */
31    public GLBL_TriggerHandler bind(Evt event, HandlerInterface eh)
32    {
33        list<HandlerInterface> handlers = eventHandlerMapping.get(event.name());
34        if (handlers == null) 
35        {
36            handlers = new list<HandlerInterface>();
37            eventHandlerMapping.put(event.name(), handlers);
38        }
39        handlers.add(eh);
40        return this;
41    }
42
43    /**
44     *   Invokes correct handlers as per the context of trigger and available registered handlers
45     */
46    public void manage()
47    {
48        Evt ev = null;
49        if(trigger.isInsert && trigger.isBefore)
50        {
51            ev = Evt.beforeinsert;
52        }
53        else if(trigger.isInsert && trigger.isAfter)
54        {
55            ev = Evt.afterinsert;
56        }
57        else if(trigger.isUpdate && trigger.isBefore)
58        {
59            ev = Evt.beforeupdate;
60        }
61        else if(trigger.isUpdate && trigger.isAfter)
62        {
63            ev = Evt.afterupdate;
64        }
65        else if(trigger.isDelete && trigger.isBefore)
66        {
67            ev = Evt.beforedelete;
68        }
69        else if(trigger.isDelete && trigger.isAfter)
70        {
71            ev = Evt.afterdelete;
72        }
73        else if(trigger.isundelete)
74        {
75            ev = Evt.afterundelete;             
76        }
77        
78        list<HandlerInterface> handlers = eventHandlerMapping.get(ev.name());
79        
80        if (handlers != null && ! handlers.isEmpty()) 
81        {
82            for (HandlerInterface h : handlers) 
83            {
84                h.handle();
85            }
86        }
87    }

136    String getEnvelope(List<RequiredSigner> requiredSigners, Boolean isDraft) {

12        Set<String> countries = new Set<String>();
13        for (Meeting_Participant_MERC__c p : participants) {

18        for (FMV_Settings_MERC__c fmvSetting : [SELECT 
19                                                    Country_Code_MERC__c, 
20                                                    Tier_Value_MERC__c,

29            } else {

31                fmvMap.put(fmvSetting.Country_Code_MERC__c, fmvList);

33        }

35        for (Meeting_Participant_MERC__c p : participants) {

38

357    public PageReference doSearch(){
358        removeAccountError = false;
359        
360        searchAccount.FirstName = searchAccount.FirstName != null ? (searchAccount.FirstName.length() > 0 ? String.escapeSingleQuotes(searchAccount.FirstName.trim()) : '') : '';

364        searchAddress.City_GLBL__c = searchAddress.City_GLBL__c != null ? (searchAddress.City_GLBL__c.length() > 0 ? String.escapeSingleQuotes(searchAddress.City_GLBL__c.trim()) : '') : '';
365        searchAddress.Zip_Postal_Code_GLBL__c = searchAddress.Zip_Postal_Code_GLBL__c != null ? (searchAddress.Zip_Postal_Code_GLBL__c.length() > 0 ? String.escapeSingleQuotes(searchAddress.Zip_Postal_Code_GLBL__c.trim()) : '') : '';
366

368

372            ApexPages.addMessage(new ApexPages.Message(ApexPages.Severity.Info, System.Label.Search_Term_Required_MVN));
373            return null;
374        }
375
376        //Pick search path: Only Accounts, Addresses, SOSL Phone
377        if (!String.isBlank(searchAccount.Phone)) {
378            searchResults = buildPhoneSearchResults();
379        } else if (String.isBlank(searchAddress.City_GLBL__c) && String.isBlank(searchAddress.St_Cd_GLBL__c) && String.isBlank(searchAddress.Zip_Postal_Code_GLBL__c)) {

381        } else {
382            searchResults = buildAddressSearchResults();
383        }

387            return null;
388        }
389
390        if (searchResults.size() >= SEARCHLIMIT) {
391            searchResults = new List<PersonSearchResultMockMVN>();
392            ApexPages.addMessage(new ApexPages.Message(ApexPages.Severity.Info, System.Label.Too_Many_Results_MVN));
393        } else if (searchResults.size() == 0 ) {
394            searchResults = new List<PersonSearchResultMockMVN>();
395            ApexPages.addMessage(new ApexPages.Message(ApexPages.Severity.Info, System.Label.No_Search_Results_MVN));
396        }
397
398        if(searchResults == null) searchResults = new List<PersonSearchResultMockMVN>();
399        didSearch = true;
400        showNewButton = true;
401        return null;
402    }

457    public List<PersonSearchResultMockMVN> buildPhoneSearchResults () {
458
459        //Do initial query

461        if(queryString == null) {
462            return null;

471            return null;

473
474        //Set up Maps and lists needed
475        LIST<LIST<SObject>> results = soslResult;
476        List<Account> acctResults = new List<Account>();
477        List<Address_GLBL__c> addrResults = new List<Address_GLBL__c>();
478        //AccountId_AddressId to the Mock Result
479        Map<String,PersonSearchResultMockMVN> uResults = new Map<String,PersonSearchResultMockMVN>();
480        
481        Map<Id,Account> acctIds = new Map<Id,Account>();
482
483        //Separate out what kind each list is
484        for(List<SObject> oneKind : results) {
485            if(oneKind.size() > 0) {
486                String typeId = oneKind[0].Id;
487                if(typeId.startsWith(acctPrefix)) {
488                    acctResults = (List<Account>) oneKind;
489                } else if(typeId.startsWith(addrPrefix)) {
490                    addrResults = (List<Address_GLBL__c>) oneKind;
491                }
492            }
493        }
494
495        //Get related Addresses
496        for(Account a : acctResults) {
497            acctIds.put(a.Id,a);
498            if (String.isBlank(searchAddress.City_GLBL__c) && String.isBlank(searchAddress.St_Cd_GLBL__c) && String.isBlank(searchAddress.Zip_Postal_Code_GLBL__c)) {
499                uResults.put(a.Id,new PersonSearchResultMockMVN(a));
500            }
501        }
502
503        Set<Id> idSet = acctIds.keySet();
504        String qString = 'SELECT ' + ADDRESSFIELDS + ' FROM Address_GLBL__c ' + buildAddressWhereClause() + ' AND Account_GLBL__c in :idSet' + ADDRESSORDERBY + ' LIMIT ' + SEARCHLIMIT;
505        List<Address_GLBL__c> subAddrs = database.query(qString);
506        addrResults.addAll(subAddrs);
507
508        for(Address_GLBL__c addr : addrResults) {
509            Account acct = new Account(Id = addr.Account_GLBL__c);
510            acct.FirstName = addr.Account_GLBL__r.FirstName;
511            acct.LastName = addr.Account_GLBL__r.LastName;
512            acct.Mdl_Nm_GLBL__c = addr.Account_GLBL__r.Mdl_Nm_GLBL__c;
513            acct.RecordTypeId = addr.Account_GLBL__r.RecordTypeId;
514
515            String key = acct.Id + '_' + addr.Id;
516            if (!uResults.containsKey(key)) {
517                if(uResults.containsKey(acct.Id)) {
518                    PersonSearchResultMockMVN psr = uResults.remove(acct.Id);
519                    psr.setAddress(addr);
520                    uResults.put(key,psr);
521                } else {
522                    uResults.put(key,new PersonSearchResultMockMVN(acct,addr));
523                }
524            }
525        }
526
527        return uResults.values();
528    }

530    public String buildSOSLString(){
531        //Put together final query and error check it
532        String qString = 'FIND {';
533        String findString = '';
534
535        //Cannot search for phone numbers with punctuation
536        findString = searchAccount.Phone.replaceAll('[^0-9]', '');
537        if (findString.length() < 2) {
538            ApexPages.addMessage(new ApexPages.Message(ApexPages.Severity.Info, System.Label.SOSL_Phone_Search_Min_Char_MVN + ' ' + findString));
539            return null;
540        }
541
542        qString += findString + '} IN PHONE FIELDS RETURNING ';
543        qString += ' Address_GLBL__c (' + ADDRESSFIELDS;
544        qString += buildAddressWhereClause();
545        qString += ADDRESSORDERBY;
546        qString += '), ';
547        qString += ' Account (' + ACCOUNTFIELDS;
548        qString += buildAccountWhereClause();
549        qString += ACCOUNTORDERBY;
550        qString += ') ';
551
552        return qString;
553    }
554
555    public String buildAccountWhereClause() {
556        String acctString = '';
557        acctString +=' WHERE IsDeleted = false ';
558
559        Map<String,String> fieldMap = new Map<String,String>();
560        fieldMap.put('LastName like',searchAccount.LastName);
561        fieldMap.put('FirstName like',searchAccount.FirstName);
562        fieldMap.put('Mdl_Nm_GLBL__c like',searchAccount.Mdl_Nm_GLBL__c);
563
564        for(String field : fieldMap.keySet()) {
565            String sTerm = fieldMap.get(field);
566            if(sTerm != null && !String.isBlank(sTerm)){
567                acctString += ' AND (' + field + ' \'' + sTerm.replaceAll('\\*', '%') + '\')';
568            }
569        }
570
571        if(recordTypeText == 'All') {
572            acctString += ' AND (RecordTypeId in :validRecordTypeIds)';
573        } else {
574            acctString += ' AND (RecordTypeId = \'' + recordTypeText + '\')';
575        }
576
577        return acctString;
578    }
579
580    public String buildAddressWhereClause() {
581        String addrString = ' WHERE IsDeleted = false ';
582
583        Map<String,String> fieldMap = new Map<String,String>();
584        fieldMap.put('City_GLBL__c like',searchAddress.City_GLBL__c);
585        fieldMap.put('St_Cd_GLBL__c =',searchAddress.St_Cd_GLBL__c);
586        fieldMap.put('Zip_Postal_Code_GLBL__c like',searchAddress.Zip_Postal_Code_GLBL__c);
587        fieldMap.put('Adrs_Cntry_Cd_GLBL__c =',searchAddress.Adrs_Cntry_Cd_GLBL__c);
588        fieldMap.put('Account_GLBL__r.LastName like',searchAccount.LastName);
589        fieldMap.put('Account_GLBL__r.FirstName like',searchAccount.FirstName);
590        fieldMap.put('Account_GLBL__r.Mdl_Nm_GLBL__c like',searchAccount.Mdl_Nm_GLBL__c);
591
592        for(String field : fieldMap.keySet()) {
593            String sTerm = fieldMap.get(field);
594            if(sTerm != null && !String.isBlank(sTerm)){
595                addrString += ' AND (' + field + ' \'' + sTerm.replaceAll('\\*', '%') + '\')';
596            }
597        }
598
599        if(recordTypeText == 'All') {
600            addrString += ' AND (Account_GLBL__r.RecordTypeId in :validRecordTypeIds)';
601        } else {
602            addrString += ' AND (Account_GLBL__r.RecordTypeId = \'' + recordTypeText + '\')';
603        }
